tiger eyes is a 2012 film directed by lawrence blume based on the 1981 young adult novel of the same name , written by judy blume and stars willa holland , amy jo johnson and tatanka means .   it follows the story of davey , a young girl attempting to cope with the sudden death of her father and the subsequent uprooting of her life .   the film marks the first major motion picture adaptation from the work of author judy blume , whose books have sold more than 82 million copies in 41 countries .